{"word":"ἄκλαυστος","slug":"ἄκλαυστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄκλαυστος</b></el> <p/><i>unlamented</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: (<el>κλαίω</el>):<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>unwept</i>, <el>φίλων</el> by friends, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>ἄκλαυτα τέκνα</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> children <i>not liable to death</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>not weeping, tearless</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b> = <el>χαίρων</el>, <i>with impunity</i>.<p/></div>"}]}